Feature exploration
===================

- Dark & Light mode colors

- Client-server mode: explore passing the client machine name (hostname)
  to the server so each client can have its own per-machine settings
  (profile, USE flags, keywords, masks) stored on the server side.  This
  would allow a single server to reason on behalf of multiple heterogeneous
  clients without each client needing its own knowledge base or config.

Investigation tasks
===================

- Investigate neovim domain assumptions: dev-python/tree-sitter-0.25.2
  requires >=dev-libs/tree-sitter-0.25*:= while neovim requires
  >=dev-libs/tree-sitter-0.26*:=.  These wildcard ranges are disjoint,
  causing a version conflict.  The prover should be able to backtrack to
  dev-python/tree-sitter-0.24.0 (which would allow 0.26.x), but currently
  does not.  Opportunity for improved conflict-driven learning / backtracking.

Refactoring tasks
=================

- Remove memoized_search: query:memoized_search/2 is not actually memoized.
  The memoization cache was removed because model construction depends on
  mutable proof state (build_with_use, prover:assuming flags, selected_cn
  snapshots, variant overrides) that cannot be captured in a sound cache key.
  Rename to something honest (e.g. query:build_dep_model/2) and remove the
  misleading name.

- Profile data naming inconsistency: the live-loading predicates use plural
  forms (e.g. profile:profile_use_terms) while the cached predicates use
  singular forms (e.g. profiledata:use_term/1).  The module split between
  profile.pl and profiledata is also inconsistent — consider unifying the
  naming convention and consolidating the interface so live and cached paths
  use the same predicate names.
